##Class #SkCanvas

SkCanvas() references one of several devices, which define how the output of drawing is represented.
As examples, a raster canvas is backed by pixels; an accelerated canvas is backed by a GPU;
a document canvas is backed by a PDF file. The type of device is specified when the canvas is
constructed. Once a canvas has been constructed, the device type can't be changed.

##Table #SkCanvas_construction
# #SkCanvas # no device, no dimensions ##
# #SkCanvas_2 # no device, set dimensions ##
# #MakeRasterDirect # raster bitmap specified by SkImageInfo ##
# #MakeRasterDirectN32 # helper for MakeRasterDirect() with inline image specification ##
##ToDo incomplete ##
##Table ##

The SkCanvas may be backed by a raster bitmap provided by the caller, using #MakeRasterDirect, or
by using its helper, #MakeRasterDirectN32.

