##Method bool getProps(SkSurfaceProps*) const #getProps

##Doxygen
If the canvas has a backing device, copy into the surface properties supplied by
the caller, and return true. Otherwise, return false and leave the caller's
surface properties unchanged.
##Doxygen ##

#ToDo This seems old style. Deprecate? ##

##Example
    SkBitmap bitmap;
    SkCanvas canvas(bitmap, SkSurfaceProps(0, kRGB_V_SkPixelGeometry));
    SkSurfaceProps surfaceProps;
    SkDebugf("isRGB:%d\n", SkPixelGeometryIsRGB(surfaceProps.pixelGeometry())),
    SkAssertResult(canvas.getProps(&surfaceProps));
    SkDebugf("isRGB:%d\n", SkPixelGeometryIsRGB(surfaceProps.pixelGeometry())),
